                <head>Israelite Citizens of Legnau</head>
                <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lengnau</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-03">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 3, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="italic">Declaration of adhesion of the Israelite citizens of Lengnau,
                        to the Swiss address of sympathy to the President of the United States of
                        America.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The sad news of the death of the noble President Lincoln, by the hand of an
                    assasssin, has troubled our hearts deeply, and so great was our consternation
                    that at first we could hardly credit the horrid news. But, alas, the public
                    papers soon confirmed the horrid report and cast a gloom of sadness over our
                    spirits.</p>
                <p>As an expression of our sentiments we willingly add our names to the address of
                    sympathy of the Swiss confederation to the President of the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JACOB BRAUNSCHWEIG, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Notary</hi>. <lb/>
                    <signed>MORIZ MAIER, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Clerk</hi>.<lb/>(Thirty-nine other signatures.) </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
